https://instagram.fiad1-1.fna.fbcdn.net/.true_caption: MY <NAME> WHITE SHOW LOOK “HER BEHEADING” my inspiration behind this look came from my deep love and fascination of Marie Antoinette. I remember watching the 2006 movie over and over again at my grandmas house when I was a child. I was obsessed with the highly stylised take on renaissance fashion and depiction of women in general. I could never understood why her final execution was so gruesome. as I got older and started to understand the politics behind her punishment, I understood she was a villain. But some of the most fascinating people are villains, I wanted to create a look that portrayed the repercussions of her need for flamboyance and materialism. I hand sewed each ruffle on the skirt imbedding a pearl between each stitch. I incorporated ribbons and bows into over half on my garment. I didn’t only look at the way The last queen of France dressed her self I looked in to every inch of her life down to what bed sheets she slept in. When it came to herself she was tremendously selfish and materialism was not enough her ego overthrew her. every fine detail was covered in gold or diamonds or pearls.
